# Canonical Select Verify

{% include "runtime/partial/stage_verification_contract.md.j2" %}

For canonical_select, verify semantic equivalence only. The prompt context contains canonical_selection_candidate_list as the complete candidate set participating in canonical selection. The result has already passed mechanical validation for grouping, candidate size-group coverage, priority ordering, missing or extra selections, and unresolved-conflict derivation from omitted size groups.

Use the mechanically valid result and prompt context to identify selected charts and omitted size_group_key groups. For each selected chart whose size_group_key has same-priority alternatives in the prompt context, read the selected chart_path and the alternative chart_path values as local JSON artifacts through normal filesystem access. Verify that selection is backed by evidence that those candidates are equivalent by normalized chart content and applicability scope. Normalized chart content means row size_label and measurement name, unit, min_value, and max_value. Applicability scope means Python-computed applicability_status, country_code_list, applicability_description, evidence_path_list, source_url, and source_title. source_url and source_title are compared evidence fields, not equivalence keys.

For every omitted size_group_key group, read every maximum-priority candidate chart artifact and verify that unresolved conflict status reflects a real semantic disagreement in normalized chart content or applicability scope. Do not re-check omitted-group candidate membership, candidate priority, selected size_group_key coverage, or deterministic representative ordering in this verifier; those are mechanical validator ownership.
